  "commentary": "With SPX at 6598.2 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6500 (-4.7B) and the positive gamma ceiling at 6605 (+2.5B), dealers are caught in a precarious hedging position where any move will force amplifying flows. The breakout regime with -4.1B total GEX means dealers are short gamma and must chase price—they'll be forced buyers on any dip toward 6500 and sellers on pushes above 6605, creating whipsaw conditions in this narrow 105-point range. Key inflection points are the 6500 max negative gamma level where dealer buying pressure intensifies, and the 6605 resistance where dealer selling kicks in hard.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile ping-pong action between 6500 and 6605 with sharp moves in either direction.",
